    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/16709430980141916851" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">cchang</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=1496#comment-6095"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-04-24T15:30:00-04:00">Tuesday, April 24, 2007 at 3:30 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Does it make you feel any better if I say that the Asparagus vinaigrette is quite yummy?</></>I think we&#8217;ve all had awful weeks like that. By far my most horrific memory was not timing the additions of various vegetable for a soup I was making correctly out of nervousness (I sort of dumped them all in) and discovering that the broccoli had turned to mush. My rice noodles also turned mushy.</></>This was the first meal I ever cooked for my in-laws and after my husband mentioned how much I liked to cook, my brother-in-law snarked &#8220;she really needs to practice more then&#8221; It really damaged my ego.</p>
    </div>

